				\begin{document}$$ {Y}_j={\mathrm{N}}_j\times {\mathrm{F}}_j\times \left(1-{\mathrm{VC}}_j\right) $$\end{document}Yj=Nj×Fj×1−VCjwhere NJ is the female population size for that spatial unit, j, Fj is the number of live births per female in the region (North, Central, and South) that contains spatial unit j, and VCj is the estimated vaccination coverage for that spatial unit j. Hereafter, we refer to Yj as the susceptible birth cohort.

