				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{G}\left(\mathrm{t}\right)=\frac{\ln \left({\mathrm{S}}_t\right)}{\mathrm{t}} $$\end{document}Gt=lnSttwhere St is the 33rd percentile of cases and t is the time it took for the first 33rd percentile of cases to present to health facilities within a polygon. We chose the first 33% of cases as this was early enough in the epidemic that dynamics were still in the exponential growth phase; consistent with the assumptions of [24]. F is assumed to be 0.5.
